# WM 2026 Office Cup — environment
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. EVERYTHING here is optional for local dev:
# with NO variables set, the app runs on the in-memory mock store (zero setup).

# --- Database (optional) ---
# When set, the app uses Neon Postgres + Drizzle. When UNSET, it uses the
# in-memory mock store automatically (good for local dev, demos, and a
# zero-config Vercel preview). Get a free URL from the Vercel Neon integration.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require

# --- Results feed ---
# Results AUTO-INGEST. The /api/cron/sync job pulls each match's outcome once it
# is due (now >= kickoff + buffer: 3h group / 3.5h knockout) and stores it as an
# authoritative 'feed' result, then recomputes the tables. No live polling.
#
# PRIMARY source is ESPN's free, NO-KEY scoreboard API — nothing to configure,
# it already serves real WC2026 results. openfootball (also free, no key) is the
# fallback. The organizer can override any winner by hand on /organizer (source
# 'organizer' always wins over the feed). Accuracy is intact with zero config.
#
# API-Football is now OPTIONAL redundancy (NOT required): set a key only if you
# want a third source. Channel is selected by API_FOOTBALL_HOST:
#   unset / 'v3.football.api-sports.io'  -> api-sports.io direct (x-apisports-key)
#   'api-football-v1.p.rapidapi.com'     -> RapidAPI (x-rapidapi-key + host)
# With no key this source is skipped entirely.
# API_FOOTBALL_KEY=
# API_FOOTBALL_HOST=v3.football.api-sports.io

# --- Cron protection (REQUIRED for the cron route to run) ---
# Shared secret the cron route checks (Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>).
# /api/cron/sync FAILS CLOSED: with no secret set it returns 503 and does
# nothing, so it can never be hit unauthenticated. Vercel cron jobs send this
# automatically when configured in vercel.json.
# CRON_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# --- Organizer access ---
# The code that unlocks the /organizer surface. The organizer is an OPTIONAL
# OVERRIDE on top of auto-ingestion, not a required confirmation step.
# In the mock store a default is baked in; set this in production.
# ORGANIZER_CODE=MP-ORGZ-0000-0000
